Howto reduce Jack XRUN when playing low latency MIDI Music

* cpu frequency governor performance:
    sudo cpufreq-set -g performance

* systemd/journald storage to RAM (done automatically when using
  meta-mortsgna/xfce4-music-image):
    /etc/systemdjournald.conf: Storage=volatile

* RT kernel setup /etc/limits.d/95-audio-tweaks.conf (see meta-qt5-extra/audio-tweaks)

* Avoid autostart of pulseaudio (Session/Autostart)

* Pi3: Disable Wifi (dtoverlay=pi3-disable-wifi)



Setup new music image:

* BACKUP DAW SESSIONS
* REMOVE NETWORK PLUG

root:
* /etc/sddm.conf -> User for autologin
* systemctl disable brcm43438
* systemctl disable serial-getty@ttyS0
* systemctl disable serial-getty@ttyAMA0
* in /usr/share/alsa/alsa.conf: Entries (check soundcards with aplay -L)
  * defaults.ctl.card 0 -> defaults.ctl.!card "sndrpihifiberry"
  * defaults.pcm.card 0 -> defaults.pcm.!card "sndrpihifiberry"
* mv /usr/share/alsa/alsa.conf.d/50-pulseaudio.conf /usr/share/alsa/alsa.conf.d/50-pulseaudio.conf_
* mv /usr/share/alsa/alsa.conf.d/99-pulseaudio-default.conf /usr/share/alsa/alsa.conf.d/99-pulseaudio-default.conf_
* audioinjector: enable mixer control "Output Mixer HiFi"
* passwd

user
* passwd
* check session autostart (blueman/baloo..)
* reduce screen resolution (yes really tested: 1280x1024 / 1280x720 are fine)
* restart
* network plug
* check journalctl output
* check systemd-analyse: Can be 8-9s
* datetime: timezone
* jack
* qtractor...
* fluid-dssi


